reviewText: As sometimes happens in real life, this movie is less about the wedding couple and more about the guests.  It attempts to make the viewer privvy to the humorous interactions that can ensue when two families meet.  However, due to disjointed writing, undeveloped acting and an overdose of caricatures, the viewer is left feeling like the honeymoon phase never started.  Six bucks wasted!
Great movie for the ages! Very funny and warm hearted for the family. A must see!
This movie is hilarious and has an Allstar cast! A must see!
Classic Romeo and Juliet story...a couple from different sides of the track brought together by love! Cute independent movie
Great movie!!
Hilarious in the most unexpected way. Very smart. Very funny.
A fun romp of a film. I thoroughly enjoyed the silly sweetness and the diverse cast of characters.

ALTON & KENYA'S OUTRAGEOUS WEDDING is an entertaining & funny look at all of the behind the scenes madness surrounding the wedding of a couple who come from different sides of the tracks.  Likeable cast and some good performances made this an enjoyable movie to watch!  Great to see some recognizable faces like Debra Wilson from MAD TV and Hayley Marie Norman from TOP FIVE.

Alton and Kenya get married in spite of the "DC thing." We get briefly introduced to a group of poorly developed characters and then on to the wedding and reception where there is a lot of gossip, but there is nothing outrageous. In fact it was very tame. One of the characters was a white guy who had a fear of black people. The script was boring and terrible.

You would be better off watching "Jumping the Broom" again.

Guide: No swearing, sex, or nudity. Some adult talk.
Loved it!  Too Funny!  I've been to many crazy weddings in my day... this one takes the cake.  Check out this great indie flick!
